keyPolicies.policyDescription: The leaflet mentions that Labour guarantees if your GP suspects you have cancer you have a right to see a specialist within two weeks and the right to be treated within 18 weeks.

issues.health: Mentions early cancer diagnosis and Labour's two-week specialist appointment guarantee.

endorsements.endorsement: Expresses gratitude towards the healthcare system for early detection and treatment of her pre-cancerous cells, and highlights Labour's role.

quotes.text: I was devastated when a scan showed that I had pre-cancerous cells in one of my breasts - it's the sort of thing you think will never happen to you. It felt like my whole life just stopped.

images.caption: A photo of Diane Dwelly with a quote about her experience with pre-cancerous cells in her breast.
